  bus at all as you are washing the oil from the cylinder walls.

>wouldn't I have gas in my oil then??

> You probably have got some but it will also be evaporated out when the oil heats up.

That's not exactly true. Some will be retained in suspension in the
oil. A smog tech told me that many emissions test failures can be
avoided by changing the oil on a car that was previously running rich
before a smog test for this very reason.
